#download VMware PowerCLI 
> https://developer.vmware.com/web/tool/vmware-powercli

#install Module
#https://developer.vmware.com/docs/13638/powercli-12-3-0-user-s-guide/GUID-16EBB87F-E6DF-430C-AFE2-4737B24247A0.html
> Install-Module 

#You must set the exeution Policy of WIndows Powerchell to RemoteSigned. 
> Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned

#Configure the PowerCLI response to Untrusted Certificates 
> Set-PowerCLIConfiguration -InvalidCertificateAction Ignore 
 - option : 
      Unset  : This is the default value and corresponds to Fail 
      Fail   : PowerCLI does not establish a connection if a certificate is not valid.
      Ignore : PowerCLI ingnores certificate validity and establishes a connection. 
      Warn   : PowerCLI logs a warning message that a certificate is not valid, displays additional information about the certificate, and establishes the connection. 
      Prompt : if a server certificate is not valid, PowerCLI prompts you to choose an action before it continuses. You can Choose one of the following options. 
      
#Create csv file 
> get-vm | Export-csv -path filename.csv



